cs.NI, cs.MA, cs.SY, cs.IT, cs.PF 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper investigates the impact of node speed on the throughput of wireless charging stations overlaid mobile networks. This falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) - The paper uses a two-dimensional Markov chain to model the energy status and distance of nodes to the nearest WCS. This technique is commonly used in multiagent systems. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper deals with the control of energy provision to mobile nodes in a wireless charging system. This falls under the domain of systems and control. 
4. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper calculates the throughput scaling of the system, which involves information theory concepts such as capacity scaling. 
5. cs.PF (Performance) - The paper investigates the impact of node speed on the throughput of the system, which is a performance metric.
